<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF86FFBDFF65FB97FDB5FB1B" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF86FFBDFF65FB97FDB5FB1B" blockId="23.[136,1452,481,1337]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFF65FB97FE8FFBEC" bold="true" box="[189,335,1093,1119]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Distribution</emphasis>
:—Endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="7ABAC0CAFF86FFBDFE21FB94FDFDFBD3" box="[505,573,1094,1120]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in Atlantic Forest Biome (
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF86FFBDFCBCFB94FBE1FBD3" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[868,1057,1094,1120]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24954" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (1997) Estudos taxonomicos de Tibouchina sect. Pleroma (D. Don) Cogn. (Melastomataceae). Tese de Doutorado. Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 191 pp." type="book" year="1997">Guimarães 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF86FFBDFBF3FB94FBA8FBD3" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[1067,1128,1094,1120]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24997" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (2012) Tibouchina. In: Baumgratz, J. F. A., Bernardo, K. F. R., Chiavegatto, B., Goldenberg, R., Guimaraes, P. J. F., Kriebel, R., Martins, A. B., Michelangeli, F. A., Reginato, M., Romero, R., Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Woodgyer, E. (Eds.) Melastomataceae: Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed July 2012)." type="url" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
). It is practically restricted to the state of 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF86FFBDFED3FBB8FE6DFB37" box="[267,429,1130,1156]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
because there is only a single specimen collected in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="C0694EB8FF86FFBDFB5AFBB8FB36FB37" box="[1154,1270,1130,1156]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, near the border between these two states (
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF86FFBDFE73FB5CFDA9FB1B" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[427,617,1166,1192]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24954" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (1997) Estudos taxonomicos de Tibouchina sect. Pleroma (D. Don) Cogn. (Melastomataceae). Tese de Doutorado. Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 191 pp." type="book" year="1997">Guimarães 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AB7D3D1FF86FFBDFF65FB63FA95FA8A" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0212805AFF86FFBDFF65FB63FA95FA8A" blockId="23.[136,1452,481,1337]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFF65FB63FEFEFB78" bold="true" box="[189,318,1201,1227]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF86FFBDFDC5FB61FD73FB7F" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Desrousseaux" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[541,691,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFDC5FB61FD73FB7F" box="[541,691,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">T. granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. It is distinguished mainly by the winged branches, the flat leaves on both surfaces, and the adaxial surface with appressed strigose trichomes, basally thickened, 1–2-branched. 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF86FFBDFD0BFB28FC08FAA7" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Desrousseaux" baseAuthorityYear="1797" box="[723,968,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="granulosa">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFD0BFB28FC08FAA7" box="[723,968,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">Tibouchina granulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very close to 
<taxonomicName id="C5ADFBD9FF86FFBDFBAEFB29FACCFAA7" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Raddi" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1142,1292,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Tibouchina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="estrellensis">
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFBAEFB29FACCFAA7" box="[1142,1292,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">T. estrellensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as mentioned previously under the latter species. Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF86FFBDFCE2FACCFBC7FA8B" author="Guimaraes, P. J. F." box="[826,1031,1310,1336]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" refId="ref24954" refString="Guimaraes, P. J. F. (1997) Estudos taxonomicos de Tibouchina sect. Pleroma (D. Don) Cogn. (Melastomataceae). Tese de Doutorado. Universidade Estadual de Campinas, Campinas, 191 pp." type="book" year="1997">Guimarães (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="663CFDABFF86FFBDFB9AFACCFA91FA8A" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Souza, M. L. D. R. &amp; Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A." box="[1090,1361,1310,1337]" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="591 - 646" refId="ref22935" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Souza, M. L. D. R., Carraca, D. C. &amp; Abbas, B. A. (2006) Melastomataceae na Reserva Biologica de Poco das Antas, Silva Jardim, Rio de Janeiro, Brasil: aspectos floristicos e taxonomicos. Rodriguesia 57 (3): 591 - 646." type="journal article" year="2006">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis id="30D95C48FF86FFBDFB1CFACDFB3CFA8B" box="[1220,1276,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
